From Michael Mauldin Subject Re Dorothy Denning opposes Clipper, Capstone wiretap chips In article A Mike Godwin writes In article C BJ BK Jim Hart writes The security of the system should depend only on the secrecy of the keys and not on the secrecy of the algorithms Dorothy Denning Cite source, please Dorothy Denning, Cryptography and Data Security , , Addison Wesley Page , under the heading Cryptosystems must satisfy three general requirements The other two are efficiency and ease of use Michael L Mauldin Carnegie Mellon University